    "description": "A high-quality genome sequence of alkaligrass provides insights into halophyte stress tolerance.\nA high-quality chromosome-level genome sequence of alkaligrass assembled from Illumina, PacBio and 10\u00d7 Genomics reads combined with genome-wide chromosome conformation capture (Hi-C) data. The \u223c1.50 Gb assembled alkaligrass genome encodes 38,387 protein-coding genes, and 54.9% of the assembly are transposable elements, with long terminal repeats being the most abundant. Comparative genomic analysis coupled with stress-treated transcriptome profiling uncovers a set of unique saline- and alkaline-responsive genes in alkaligrass",
